2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the prediction of forces on finger tips, which is relevant to robotics. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses a recurrent neural network for action prediction. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper uses machine learning techniques for action prediction. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely sub-category, but it is relevant as the paper evaluates human observers' skills in predicting actions from video sequences.
